The paper discusses the analysis of scientific publications and their coauthors, which falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as it deals with the study of collaboration networks among researchers. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is also a likely category as it involves the analysis of publications and their impact. cs.CY (Computational Geometry) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are possible categories as they deal with the analysis of data and patterns. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible category as it involves the study of scientific publications and their retrieval.
